John Steenhuisen has been elected DA leader at the party's virtual congress on Sunday. Steenhuisen beat opponent KwaZulu-Natal MPL Mbali Ntuli, receiving 80% of votes cast. Meanwhile, Helen Zille retained her position as federal council chair, with 69% of votes. Presiding officers said the online voting platform worked well during South Africa's first virtual congress. "The election results were compliant with all DA election requirements and rules. They were signed off by us, as presiding officers, as well as the candidates' party agents and also a professional audit firm who acted as independent external auditors and who oversaw the voting process," they said. Steenhuisen has been the party's interim leader following Mmusi Maimaine's shocking resignation from the party in October 2019. Other elected leaders include: HeraldLIVE